babel cli - babel command line
    installation: npm i -g babel-cli

installing babel for es6 es7
    - yarn add babel-preset-env
        - the env is the library that works with es5, es6, es7

installing babel for react:
    - yarn add babel-preset-react

commands:
    babel --help > help

compile with babel:
    - in terminal, in the project folder:
        - babel (name of input folder) --out-file=(name of output file) --presets=(wanted compilers seperated by coma), for example:
        - babel src/app.js --out-file=public/scripts/app.js --presets=env,react --watch
            - babel src/app.js --out-file=public/bundle.js --presets=env,react --watch
        - watch is for setting watch compiler
